\par
\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \fi300 Varieties of Malay typically use \i ada \i0 as the existential. SLM however has also recruited \i duuduk \i0 for this purpose. \i Duuduk \i0 can only be used with animate referents. Besides the use as an existential, it also retains its old meaning of \lquote to sit\rquote  and the extended meaning of \lquote to reside\rquote . These two meanings are also found in other varieties of Malay. What is not found is the fully grammaticalized existential as in ({\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BMex_exist_slm_bats \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{2.4}}}).\par
