}\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \fi300 Tamil has no such construction. But Malay varieties do have comparable devices: the \i kena\i0 -construction and the prefixes \i ter- \i0 and \i ke-\i0 .\par
\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \fi300 The \i kena\i0 -construction ({Chung} 2005) is used to express adversative events and thus shares the meaning of involuntary involvement in the event.{\up16\chftn}
{\*\footnote \pard\plain\s246\f13\fs20 {\up16\chftn}In Malaysia, \i kena \i0 has a second meaning of \lquote obligation\rquote  ({Wahab & Nomoto} 2010). This meaning is not found in Sri Lanka.}
