\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \sb120 \fi0 {\s4\ql\sb240\sa60\keepn\f13\b\fs32 {\*\bkmkstart BMex_nmlz_tam}2.8{\*\bkmkend BMex_nmlz_tam}  Zero adclausal nominalization\par
}\pard\qj\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 Sinhala and Tamil differ in the way they encode argument clauses. In Tamil, all clauses which serve as an argument of a verb are necessarily nominalized, usually with \i adu\i0 . In the following example, the nominalizer is found between the stem and the accusative case marker. Leaving out the nominalizer would lead to ungrammaticality.\par
